{{harvnb |Sa'di |2007 |pp=297 |ps=, "at least 780,000 ... more than 80 percent"}}</ref> Eleven Arab towns and cities, and [[List of towns and villages depopulated during the 1947–1949 Palestine war|over 500 villages]] were destroyed or depopulated.<ref name="500 villages">{{harvnb |Abu-Laban |Bakan |2022 |p=511}};
{{harvnb |Manna |2022 |p=17}};
{{harvnb |Pappe |2022 |ps=, pp. 121 and 128 ("Half of the villages had been destroyed, flattened by Israeli bulldozers ...")}};
{{harvnb |Khalidi |2020 |p=73 |ps=, "conquest and depopulation ... of scores of Arab cities, towns, and villages"}};
